SIMPLE: foretop
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foretop
<hw>Fore"top`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The hair
on the forepart of the head; esp., a tuft or lock of hair which hangs
over the forehead, as of a horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That part of a headdress that is in front; the top
of a periwig.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The platform at the head of the
foremast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fore-topgallant</ent>⟦br⟧
